  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large clay pot or Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, cinnamon, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper. Cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the fish and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side, until browned.",
    "Add the dried prunes and enough water to cover the fish. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 10-12 minutes, or until the fish is cooked through.",
    "Stir in the chopped parsley. Serve the fish hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired.",
    "Serve the fish with the rich tagine sauce spooned over the top."
